The paper deals with the optimization of energy efficiency and data compression in the context of the Internet of Things, which involves wireless communication and information theory. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) are the most likely categories. The paper also proposes an offline optimal policy for allocating energy and transmission parameters, which involves control theory and optimization, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a likely category as well. Additionally, the paper mentions data compression, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
